50|$|The Thomas Rees Memorial <b>Carillon</b> is a <b>carillon</b> {{located in}} Washington Park in Springfield, Illinois. The brutalist tower stands 132 feet and is {{constructed}} from concrete, brick and steel. It was dedicated in 1962 and designed by Bill Turley. Each year the <b>carillon</b> hosts the International <b>Carillon</b> Festival which features world-renowned carillonneurs.|$|R
